Photos from the Inland Empire's 2nd annual Premier Hackathon. Where the best and brightest competed in a 36 hour hacking showdown, right in the heart of Riverside.

Photo credits: Alyza Malunao, Nancy Gao, Patrick Le, and Dayo Adeleke! With some edits by Nancy Gao!

10.27.16 - Citrus Hack 2016: Thank You Sponsors!

We would like to thank our sponsors one more time for helping us host such a fruitful event. If you haven't been able to check out these companies or organizations, make sure you do! You won't be disappointed! #CitrusHack2016 Cee out!

10.24.16 - Citrus Hack 2016: Thank You!

After a weekend of fun and innovation, Citrus Hack 2016 has come to an end. We want to thank everyone who came out and made this event awesome. Continue working on your projects, break through every boundary you see and we will see you next year! #CitrusHack2016

10.23.16 - CITRUS HACK 2016: Day THREE 

It's the last day of hacking, are you ready for the final stretch? Polish whatcha got and rock those demos. Best of luck to all attendees! If you haven't already sign up for our slack for in-event details at https://citrushack2016.slack.com/signup. #CitrusHack2016

10.22.16 - CITRUS HACK 2016: Day TWO

Day Two is here! How are your projects coming along? Our live site is up for info on prizes, schedules, and more on #CitrusHack2016 at citrushack.com. Sign up for our slack for in-event details at https://citrushack2016.slack.com/signup.

10.21.16 - CITRUS HACK 2016

Today is the big day, #CitrusHack2016 is underway. Check in has started outside of Winston Chung Hall next to North Campus Drive: http://campusmap.ucr.edu. Sign up for our slack for in-event details. https://citrushack2016.slack.com/signup.

10.20.16 - 1 More Day: SupplyFrame 

Get your soldering irons warmed up and your laptops charged, Citrus Hack is tomorrow! Are you ready for some hardware and software hacking? Check out the Hackaday community for some projects others have done, hackaday.io/projects. #CitrusHack2016 goes live tomorrow, catch the experience on our social media.

10.19.16 - 2 More Days: Co-Sponsor Equipo Vision

Today we are very excited to announce Equipo Vision as our Co-Hosting Sponsor for Citrus Hack 2016! Their continued support for Citrus Hack has and will allow us to offer you an awesome hackathon. Don't forget #CitrusHack2016 will be the hub for important social media updates this weekend!

10.18.16 - 3 More Days: Facebook

It's the final countdown, with three days left we hope you are ready for this weekend. Of course we have to shoutout our sponsor Facebook for hooking us up with some swag and supporting Citrus Hack! Stay up to date with all things Citrus Hack on our social media, #CitrusHack2016.

10.17.16 - 4 More Days: Google

As the final countdown continues, there are just four days left until Citrus Hack 2016. We've got the support of the search giant, Google, and this weekend we will support you! More updates to come on our social media, keep it locked on #CitrusHack2016.

10.16.16 - 5 More Days: HackerEarth, BitPeel, & GitHub

With five days left until Citrus Hack, there is still time to practice and get some accounts set up to show off what you make! We are proud to be sponsored by tech companies that support student developers! HackerEarth is a site for programming challenges and developer jobs, BitPeel works with all things Ruby and GitHub is a project hosting master. Keep your eyes on our social media for updates to come  on #CitrusHack2016.

10.15.16 - 6 More Days: ASPB & The YESman

Six days left until Citrus Hack 2016! Do you have a team and a project in mind? This year we have Denis Nurmela/Speaker from The YESman giving a talk on Hacking Life and UC Riverside Associated Students Program Board (ASPB) providing food to make sure you have plenty of energy to hack the weekend away! Stay tuned for more news on #CitrusHack2016.

10.14.16 - 7 Day Sponsor Countdown

There is one week remaining until our weekend of innovation. We will be counting down with some hints to the prizes to be won thanks to our wonderful sponsors. Today we would like to thank Amazon.com and GIGABYTE for sponsoring Citrus Hack 2016! Stay posted on our social media for updates on #CitrusHack2016.

10.10.16 - Acceptances Round Two!

We hope this makes your Monday a little better. We have sent out another round of acceptance emails! Once you see the email, make sure you confirm that you will attend. In the meantime, we are still accepting applications for the waitlist. If you have yet to register, head to citrushack.com and sign up for a weekend of innovation.

10.09.16 - Volunteers Assemble!  

Wanna help out behind the scenes? We know Cee does. Citrus Hack is now accepting volunteer applications for UCR STUDENTS to help run the event! If you would like to help fill out the following form and get ready to make this a great weekend of innovation! Form link: goo.gl/jW6fQX

10.06.16 - Soylent & Starbucks

Sponsors make hackathons possible and these companies make sure you can keep going. We are proud to announce Soylent and Starbucks as Citrus Hack sponsors. Get fueled up on Soylent and get the chance to win a couple Starbucks goodies!

10.04.16 - Acceptances & Registration

We have started sending out our acceptance emails, once you see the email don't forget to confirm that you are going! Due to popular demand, we are opening registration for those who missed the deadline. Applications that come in now will be put on a waitlist and will be notified if accepted.

10.01.16 - Registration Closes TONIGHT

Pause the Netflix & put down the Snapchat. You do not want to procrastinate on this. Registration for Citrus Hack closes tonight at midnight. Sign yourself up for a weekend of innovation. Apply now at citrushack.com!

09.28.16 - Don't wait for the Weekend

Can't wait until the weekend? Well, don't let the weekend pass you by without registering for Citrus Hack! Registration closes in 3 days on Saturday, October 1st at midnight. Apply now at citrushack.com.

09.26.16 - Facebook Event + Registration Close

Before I begin, allow me to introduce myself. I am Cee Highlander, a Shiba Citrus mix and the mascot for Citrus Hack. I'll be stopping by every now and then for some announcements!

We have a Facebook event created so you can see who plans on going to Citrus Hack and start forming your teams. Our registration is closing THIS Saturday, October 1st. So be sure to "citruself" down and register! Cee, signing out!

Event Link: https://www.facebook.com/events/1781588788757544/

09.16.16 - Flashback Friday

Hackathons aren't possible without the support of our Sponsors! So we're doing a Flashback Friday to our Co-Sponsor Equipo Vision from Citrus Hack 2015! If you want to support Citrus Hack and be a sponsor, contact us before it's too late! Students can still apply at citrushack.com!

09.12.16 - SD Hacks

Our friends down in San Diego are having their annual Hackathon at the end of this month! Can't wait for Citrus Hack? SD Hacks is ready for you! Sign up at sdhacks.io! Citrus Hack applications are also still open at citrushack.com!

09.06.16 - New Partner

We hope you were all able to relax and reflect this labor day weekend. Despite the end of this holiday celebration, Citrus Hack has some news worth celebrating. We have secured a new partnership and are now an MLH sanctioned event! Remember that registration is still going on strong, so reserve your spot at citrushack.com for an eventful weekend!

08.29.16 - Registration is now OPEN

The moment you have all been waiting for… registration for Citrus Hack 2016 is now OPEN! Check out our redesigned website at citrushack.com for registration, sponsors, FAQs, and much more soon to come. Make sure you hit that apply button to reserve your spot, hope to see you this fall!

08.25.16 - Start Innovating

Got a great idea but can never find the time to work on it? Innovations like the lightbulb are challenging the status quo at hackathons worldwide. Citrus Hack is coming back this fall for another 36-hour hackathon. Registration opens 08.29.16.

fact no. 54 - Charging on the Go

Hackathons are great places to learn something new, but we thought you shouldn't have to wait until our event! Hopefully, the facts we post can inspire you to create, innovate and explore. First up, fact no. 54.

Ready for the next iteration of the Inland Empire's Premier Hackathon?! Citrus Hack is coming back to the University of California, Riverside this fall. The event will take place October 21st - October 23rd, 2016. Make sure you mark your calendars and get ready for 36 hours of hacking!

Hackathons are not just a great way for students to have fun but they are great ways to network and prepare yourself for future projects! Don't believe us? Microsoft thinks so too! What do you expect to get from hackathons? Fill out your thought bubble in a comment below! 

In July, Microsoft held a one week hackathon and through that one event they expect to have 275 new patents. Microsoft wants future hackathons to be just as successful so they plan on releasing their internal tools to schools further down the line. Come to Citrus Hack to build your skills and/or network with other students or professionals to beef up that resume! APPLY NOW at citrushack.com!

status_message:
Hey everyone, if you don't already know what a hackathon is or don't know how participating in one can benefit you, this article about the growing importance of hackathons from MLH is a good place to start.
http://news.mlh.io/hackathons-are-taking-the-world-by-storm-02-21-2014
The Citrus Hack team hard at work at this week's general meeting!
Had an extremely successful first recruitment event last Friday. Can't wait to see what the future has in store for us.
Happy Mother's day to all the beautiful hacker moms out there. We can't be coding endlessly without your support. Thank for always being there for us and we wish you a Fantastic Day
The Recruitment Event is starting!!!! Come to Hub 260, its upstairs, 2nd floor, in the hallway.

Hey Everyone! Remember there is a recruitment event tomorrow! 
We are looking for motivated people that want to make a difference in UCR! 

Where: Hub 260
Time: 4 - 5 pm

Tell your friends!! It open to all majors! See you there!

The Citrus Hack Crew at our tabling event today! It was a huge success! Thank you to all those who volunteered! Remember to come out to our recruitment event if you want to learn more about how to help CitrusHack!

Become a part of the team that is organizing Riverside's Premier Hackathon! We are looking for motivated people that are interested in....
- Resume Building
- Being a part of a legacy at UCR
- Gaining Experience organizing a large scale event
- Opening networking opportunities with Large Technical Corporations
- Having LOTS OF FUN!

Come join us at our table tomorrow, May 6th, from 10 - 1 pm, at the Bell Tower, if you have any questions.
Help us throw the Biggest Hackathon in the history of UCR! Come and join us for our recruitment Event next week!

Hey Guys! Remember to go to the ACM General Meeting!! This week we will have Guest Speaker Maylynn Melendez from INROADS talk about "Interview Readiness". Have an interview soon? Then don't miss out on this event!

Also, please come to the meeting if you are interested in helping for CitrusHack.

HEY EVERYONE! Today is the last day to register for HackUCI!!!!
